title: The main function for the not missing at random non-response — mnar
code: # Set seed for reproducibility set.seed(123)  # Define sample size n <- 10000  # Generate variables x1 <- rlnorm(n, 0, 1) x2 <- rexp(n, 1) x3 <-  rpois(n,2) y <- 1 + x1 + x2 + rnorm(n)  # Calculate probabilities pr <- plogis(1 + 0.5*x1 - 0.5*y)  # Create population data frame pop_data <- data.frame(x1, x2, y, pr)  # Calculate population totals totals <- c(N = n, colSums(pop_data[, c("x1", "x2", "y")]))  # Generate flag variable based on probabilities flag <- rbinom(n, 1, pop_data$pr)  # Create sample based on flag sample <- pop_data[flag == 1, ] sample$d <- n/nrow(sample)   # Case when dim(response) == dim(calibration) g <- mnar(response = ~ x1 + y,             calibration =  ~ x1 + x2,             data = sample, dweights = sample$d,             pop_totals = totals,             method = "gencalib") #> Error in sample$d: object of type 'closure' is not subsettable  head(g) #display only couple of first output values #> Error in eval(expr, envir, enclos): object 'g' not found  ## Case when dim(response) < dim(calibration) g1 <- mnar(response = ~ y,              calibration =  ~ x1 + x2,              data = sample, dweights = sample$d,              pop_totals = totals,              method = "gencalib") #> Error in sample$d: object of type 'closure' is not subsettable  head(g1) #display only couple of first output values #> Error in eval(expr, envir, enclos): object 'g1' not found
